# TRAC requirements audit — pass 1 (docs only)

When the user asks to continue TRAC pass 1, audit a TR slice, or references `requirements-audit-queue.md` in pace-trac2, follow this protocol.

## Scope

- **In scope:** Update requirement slices under `docs/requirements/TR*.md` and status rows in `docs/delivery/requirements-audit-queue.md`.
- **Out of scope:** Any edit under `src/`, tests, migrations, CSS, or pass-2 implementation. Do not update [trac-build-queue.md](../docs/delivery/trac-build-queue.md) build status.

## Authority

| Source | Role |
|--------|------|
| `pace-prototype/apps/pace-trac/` | **Layout authority** — event landing, overview/dashboard cards, planning, itinerary, costs, risks, contacts, journal |
| `pace-trac2/src/` | **Read-only** — note drift; requirements target prototype layout |
| `pace-core2/packages/core/docs/standards/` | **Component and markup rules** |
| [trac-architecture.md](../docs/requirements/trac-architecture.md) | Route ownership — use for **Implementation delta (pass 2)** when prototype routes differ |

Prototype is **layout only**. Do not copy hash router, mock store, or Tweaks panel as mandates.

## Prototype vs production (common deltas)

- Assignments: prototype uses **inline assignment on `PlanningItemPage`**; production has **`/assignments`** — spec prototype layout; note route split in pass-2 delta.
- Master plan: prototype uses **Itinerary full mode**; production may use **`/masterplan`** — both belong in TR10 visual spec with delta note.
- Event selector: prototype **`TracLandingPage`** mirrors BASE shell landing pattern.

## Procedure (each slice)

1. Read [requirements-audit-queue.md](../docs/delivery/requirements-audit-queue.md); select the lowest `audit_order` with `audit_status = Pending` (or resume `In progress`).
2. Set row to `In progress`.
3. Read the requirement doc, `prototype_refs`, and skim implementation hints (read-only).
4. Audit layout gaps: planning tabs, full-page item editor, itinerary modes, cost rollups display, risk register, journal publish flow, overview KPI/launcher cards.
5. Update **only** the requirement slice:
   - **Visual specification** (or equivalent)
   - Layout-driven acceptance criteria
   - **Prototype reference:** line with correct paths
   - **Implementation delta (pass 2)** for route or IA differences
6. Set row to `Done`.
7. Continue to next Pending slice unless the user capped the run.

## Dry run

Report gaps in chat only; do not modify files.

## Chaining

After marking Done, proceed to the next Pending slice without asking the user to repeat the audit prompt.
